# 🛡 PART 1 — SECURITY HARDENING (Critical)

## 🔐 1. Firewall (UFW)

Enable firewall immediately:

```bash
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
sudo ufw allow 22        # SSH (if needed)
sudo ufw allow 3000      # Grafana (only if LAN needed)
sudo ufw enable
```

Then restrict PostgreSQL:

Do NOT allow 5432 publicly.

Allow only LAN:

```bash
sudo ufw allow from 192.168.1.0/24 to any port 5432
```

Better:
Allow per-client IP only.

---

## 🔐 2. PostgreSQL Hardening

In:

`/etc/postgresql/*/main/postgresql.conf`

Set:

```
listen_addresses = 'localhost,192.168.1.10'
```

In `pg_hba.conf`:

Allow specific machines only:

```
host tyre_factory_db pc1_user 192.168.1.20/32 md5
host tyre_factory_db qc_user  192.168.1.25/32 md5
```

Not entire subnet.

Restart PostgreSQL.

---

## 🔐 3. Strong DB Roles

Never use postgres user in your app.

Create role per module:

* building_user
* curing_user
* qc_user
* readonly_user (for Grafana)

Limit permissions per role.

---

## 🔐 4. Fail2Ban

Protect against brute-force login:

```bash
sudo apt install fail2ban
```

Enable SSH jail.

---

## 🔐 5. Disable Unnecessary Services

Check:

```bash
sudo systemctl list-unit-files --type=service
```

Disable Bluetooth, cups, avahi if unused.

---

# ⚙ PART 2 — MINIMIZE DOWNTIME

## 🧠 1. Automatic Service Restart

Enable auto restart for PostgreSQL and Grafana:

Check:

```bash
sudo systemctl edit postgresql
```

Add:

```
Restart=always
RestartSec=5
```

Same for Grafana.

---

## 🧠 2. Enable Auto-Start on Boot

Ensure:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable postgresql
sudo systemctl enable grafana-server
```

---

## 🧠 3. Kernel Panic Auto-Reboot

Edit:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/sysctl.conf
```

Add:

```
kernel.panic = 10
```

This reboots after 10 seconds if system crashes.

---

# 💾 PART 3 — DATA PROTECTION

This is most important.

## 📦 1. Daily Automatic Backup

Create script:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
pg_dump tyre_factory_db > /home/backup/db_$(date +%F).sql
```

Add cron:

```bash
crontab -e
```

Add:

```
0 2 * * * /home/backup_script.sh
```

Daily 2AM backup.

---

## 📦 2. Weekly Full System Backup

Use:

* Timeshift
  OR
* rsync to external SSD

---

## 📦 3. Offsite Backup (Optional)

Sync backups to:

* External drive
* Or secure cloud
* Or another PC in office

Never rely on one machine only.

---

# 🔌 PART 4 — POWER & HARDWARE STABILITY

This is industrial critical.

## ⚡ 1. UPS

Mandatory.

At least:

* 30 min backup
* Enough for safe shutdown

Even better:
Install NUT (Network UPS Tools)
Auto shutdown on battery low.

---

## 💾 2. Use Good NVMe (You Already Did 👍)

Crucial Gen4 is good.

Enable SMART monitoring:

```bash
sudo apt install smartmontools
sudo smartctl -a /dev/nvme0n1
```

---

## 🌡 3. Thermal Monitoring

Install:

```bash
sudo apt install lm-sensors
```

Monitor CPU temps.

NUC in cabinet needs airflow.

---

# 📊 PART 5 — MONITORING

You already have Grafana.

Add:

* Node Exporter
* PostgreSQL Exporter

Monitor:

* CPU usage
* RAM
* Disk usage
* DB connections
* Temperature

Set alert:
If disk > 80%
If DB down
If CPU > 90%

---

# 🧱 BONUS: Reduce GUI Risk

Since you're using Ubuntu Desktop:

Disable:

* Auto updates during working hours
* Unnecessary login prompts

Set updates manually weekly.

